One function of operating systems is to generate a user interface. This is what the user of the device interacts with. This interface can be a GUI or CLI.
Another function of operating systems is security. Operating systems need to protect users passwords from unwanted access. It also needs to prevent the wrong people from accessing the operating system. 
A third function of operating systems is to handle input and output. Input can come in the for of a mouse which is then processed by the operating system. The operating system also processes and outputs information aswell.
